                                            "expression": "themecolor.theme_textcolor"
                                        }
                                    },
                                    "text": "There are circumstances where you want to use separate inputs for onset detection and descriptor analysis. This is primarily when using specialist sensors or microphone types that are good at detecting onsets but have poor sound or frequency response on their own. The various input modes of all the descriptor objects allow you to decouple onset detection from descriptor analysis giving you the best-of-both-worlds."
                                }
