                                    "text": "The first two outlets contain the descriptors, with the left-most one being a list and the second one being a buffer name to be passed onto other processes. The last two outlets are time-aligned trigger and gate outputs similar to dk.onset~ dk.onsetframe~. The list output is most useful when you want to map the values directly whereas the buffer output is better for passing between complex processes (classification, regression, corpus matching, etc...)."
