                            {
                                "box": {
                                    "id": "obj-14",
                                    "linecount": 8,
                                    "maxclass": "comment",
                                    "numinlets": 1,
                                    "numoutlets": 0,
                                    "patching_rect": [ 10.0, 81.0, 533.0, 114.0 ],
                                    "saved_attribute_attributes": {
                                        "textcolor": {
                                            "expression": "themecolor.theme_textcolor"
                                        }
                                    },
                                    "text": "You can find tune the descriptor analysis based on what you are focused on analyzing. Window and FFT size are some of the first things that can be adjusted, though you have to keep in mind the fundamental tradeoff between temporal accuracy (latency) and spectral accuracy for most descriptors. Beyond that you can adjust some algorithm-specific parameters such as the minfreq and maxfreq for computing melbands or adjust the smoothing being applied to reealtime descriptors with the history parameter. It is worth mentioning that everything in Data Knot is optimized towards lower latency, so most of the fine tuning you can do will be to improve the spectral resolution and accuracy."
                                }
                            },
